# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 2024-aluminium-alloy
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1050-aluminium-alloy] Alternate names and designations include Al99.5, 3.0255, and A91050.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1060-aluminium-alloy] 1060 aluminium alloy is an aluminium-based alloy in the "commercially pure" wrought family (1000 or 1xxx series).
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1060-aluminium-alloy] It is fundamentally very similar to 1050 aluminium alloy, with the difference coming down to 0.1% aluminium by weight.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1060-aluminium-alloy] However, while both 1050 and 1060 are covered by the same ISO standard, they are covered by different ASTM standards.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1060-aluminium-alloy] As a wrought alloy, it is typically formed by extrusion or rolling.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1060-aluminium-alloy] It is commonly used in the electrical and chemical industries, on account of having high electrical conductivity, corrosion resistance, and workability.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1060-aluminium-alloy] It has low mechanical strength compared to more significantly alloyed metals.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1060-aluminium-alloy] It can be strengthened by cold working, but not by heat treatment.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1060-aluminium-alloy] Alternate designations include Al99.6 and A91060.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1070-aluminium-alloy] It is a wrought alloy with a high corrosion resistance and an excellent brazing ability.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1070-aluminium-alloy] 1070 Aluminium alloy has aluminium, iron, silicon, zinc, vanadium, copper, titanium, magnesium, and manganese as minor elements.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1100-aluminium-alloy] Alternate designations include Al99.0Cu and A91100.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1100-aluminium-alloy] 1100 and its various tempers are covered by the ISO standard 6361 and the ASTM standards B209, B210, B211, B221, B483, B491, and B547.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1199-aluminium-alloy] 1199 aluminium alloy is an aluminium-based alloy in the "commercially pure" wrought family (1000 or 1xxx series).
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1199-aluminium-alloy] With a minimum of 99.99% aluminium, it is the purest and least alloyed of the commercial aluminium alloys.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1199-aluminium-alloy] It is soft and unsuitable for machining.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1199-aluminium-alloy] At the same time, it possesses excellent corrosion resistance, electrical conductivity, and thermal conductivity.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/1199-aluminium-alloy] Commercially pure aluminium alloys are used in applications such as conductors, capacitors, heat exchangers, packaging foil and chemical equipment.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/2024-aluminium-alloy] 2024 is commonly extruded, and also available in alclad sheet and plate forms.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/2024-aluminium-alloy] It is not commonly forged; the related 2014 aluminium alloy is, though.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/2024-aluminium-alloy] Aluminium alloy 2024 has a density of 2.78 g/cm3 (0.1 lb/in3), electrical conductivity of 30% IACS, Young's modulus of 73 GPa (10.6 Msi) across all tempers, and begins to melt at 500 °C (932 °F).
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/2024-aluminium-alloy] The mechanical properties of 2024 depend greatly on the temper of the material.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/2024-aluminium-alloy] 2024-O temper aluminium has no heat treating.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/2024-aluminium-alloy] It has an ultimate tensile strength of 140–210 MPa (21–30 ksi), and a maximum yield strength of no more than 97 MPa (14,000 psi).
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/2024-aluminium-alloy] The material has elongation (stretch before ultimate failure) of 10–25%, this is the allowable range per applicable AMS specifications.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/2024-aluminium-alloy] T3 temper 2024 sheet has an ultimate tensile strength of 400–430 MPa (58–62 ksi) and yield strength of at least 270–280 MPa (39–40 ksi).
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/2024-aluminium-alloy] Solution treated at foundry and naturally aged.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/2024-aluminium-alloy] Cooled from hot-working and artificially aged (at elevated temperature).
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/2024-aluminium-alloy] T351 temper 2024 plate has an ultimate tensile strength of 470 MPa (68 ksi) and yield strength of 280 MPa (41 ksi).
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/2024-aluminium-alloy] Due to its high strength and fatigue resistance, 2024 is widely used in aircraft, especially wing and fuselage structures under tension.
[src:2024-aluminium-alloy/2024-aluminium-alloy] Additionally, since the material is susceptible to thermal shock, 2024 is used in the qualification of liquid penetrant tests outside of normal temperature ranges.
